Compilation
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
MPI : 		mpicc –g –o mpi_conv mpi_image_conv.c –lm
OpenMP+MPI : 	mpicc –g –fopenmp opmp_mpi_conv op_mpi_image.c -lm


Execution (examples)
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
MPI : 		mpiexec –f machines –np 8 ./mpi_conv waterfall_1920_2520.raw 2520 1920 30 2 grey
OpenMP+MPI : 	mpiexec –f ompmachines –np 8 ./opmp_mpi_conv waterfall_1920_2520.raw 2520 1920 30 2
grey


Execution - Input
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Each run (in both MPI & OpenMP+MPI executables) needs to be givev as arguments the following :

[imageName] [rows number] [columns number] [max iterations] [check convergence iterations] [type of image (grey/rgb)]


Execution - Output
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Each run if succesfull produces :

a) A converted image file with full name  "conv_" & imageName

b) A log file (.mpi_log / .omp_mpi_log for each case) which appends to existent file (or creating new if does not exist) the following : 
RunDate ImageName Rows Cols MaxIterations ConvergenceIterations NumProcesses NumThreads(if used) RunTime ReadTime WriteTime


Scripts
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Scripts (tcsh) given are not for the whole testing. Better one to customize for his/her needs
